<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="920" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d920">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Newel</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-11-24"><hi rend="italic">November 24,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[Mr. Hill directs that the Government of the Netherlands and the
                            international bureau of The Hague be notified that, in conformity with
                            article 23 of Hague convention for the pacific settlement of
                            international <pb facs="0891" n="793" xml:id="pg_793"/> disputes, the
                            President designates as members of the court of arbitration ex-President
                            Benjamin Harrison, Chief Justice Melville W. Fuller, Attorney-General
                            John W. Griggs, and Judge George Gray.]</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>